A minimalist ncurses-based text editor
	
dav (dav ain't vi) is meant to provide a stable text editor that is efficient
in both memory and processor usage. it is simple to use, making it ideal for
novice users. it is licensed under the gpl and is still
in development.

features include:

    * memory and cpu efficiency
    * small filesize and footprint
    * freely licensed under the gpl
    * useful feature set
    * intuitive and easy to use


homepage http://dav-text.sourceforge.net/